### **(1) Translation into English**
**Wei Wuhou** was planning a strategy that was flawless, and none of his ministers could match his wisdom. After court, he wore a pleased expression. **Wu Qi** stepped forward and asked:
*"Have you ever heard the words of King Zhuang of Chu, as spoken to his ministers?"*
Wei Wuhou replied: *"What did King Zhuang of Chu say?"*
Wu Qi answered:
*"When King Zhuang of Chu devised a strategy that was flawless, and none of his ministers could match his wisdom, he wore a worried expression after court. **Shen Gong Wu Sun** approached and asked: ‘Your Majesty, why do you have a worried look after court?’
King Zhuang replied: ‘When I devise a strategy that is flawless and no one can match my wisdom, I worry. There is a saying from **Zhong Ni** [Confucius’ disciple]: *‘A ruler who finds a teacher becomes a king; one who finds a friend becomes a hegemon; one who finds doubt survives; but one who thinks no one can match him perishes.’*
Now, with my mediocrity, yet my ministers cannot match me—my kingdom is nearly lost! That is why I worry.’*
King Zhuang worried, but you rejoice."*

Wei Wuhou hesitated, then bowed twice: *"Heaven has sent you, Master, to correct my errors."*

